<DATELINE>BEVERLY, Mass. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Forget Park Place or Boardwalk, commissar.
Red Square beckons.
   Parker Brothers, makers of Monopoly, announced Monday that the
Soviet people may soon have the opportunity to pass Go, collect 200
rubles and conduct wild real estate deals.
   The manufacturer of the best-selling game said it has created a
Russian-language version of the game, using the Cyrillic alphabet.
   The company said it anticipates great interest once the game is
offered for sale in the Soviet Union, as the popularity of
Western-style toys and games increases in an era of glasnost, or
openness.
