<HEAD>Member of Precision Flying Team Drunk in Fatal Car Crash</HEAD>
<DATELINE>RECTOR, Pa. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A member of the Canadian Snowbirds precision
military flying team was drunk when the car he was driving crashed
into a tree, killing him and hurting two other team members,
officials say.
   Capt. Wesley MacKay, 28, had an alcohol concentration of 0.191
percent in his blood, Skip Rusciewicz, a coroner, said Monday.
Pennsylvania law recognizes 0.10 as the level of intoxication.
   The crash occurred early Saturday morning along a winding,
private road leading from Huntland Downs, the home of Seward
Prosser Mellon, an heir to the Mellon banking fortune. The Canadian
pilots were guests at a dinner party at the estate Friday evening.
   The Snowbirds were to perform over the weekend, but their
performances were canceled.
