<HEAD>Cool Autumn Air Chills Northern Plains, Northeast</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Cool autumn air chilled parts of the northern Plains and the
Northeast today and scattered showers dampened the Pacific
Northwest and Florida.
   A cold front pushed through the central Plains today, dropping
early morning temperatures into the 30s and 40s in the northern
Plains.
   Temperatures were in the 40s in New England and the northern
Appalachians because of a cool Canadian air mass centered over New
York state. Readings dropped into the 30s in some parts of Maine.
   Thunderstorms dumped locally heavy rain on parts of the Florida
Keys, and thunderstorms also were scattered over northern Florida.
   Further north, fog draped the southern and central Appalachians,
reducing visibility to near zero in parts of southeast Kentucky.
   Showers ahead of an approaching cold front scattered light rain
over the Pacific Northwest.
   Most other parts of the country enjoyed fair skies.
   Today's forecast called for showers across the Pacific Northwest
and the northern Plateau region, and northern New England. Showers
and thunderstorms were expected in Florida, Nebraska and the
Dakotas. Clouds were expected in the upper Great Lakes, but skies
were predicted to be mostly sunny elsewhere.
   Highs were forecast to be in the 50s and 60s across the
country's northern tier from New England and the northern Great
Lakes to the Pacific Northwest; and in the 90s from much of Texas
to the desert Southwest. Highs elsewhere were predicted to be
mainly in the 70s and 80s.
   At 3 a.m. EDT, temperatures ranged from 36 degrees at Concord,
N.H., and Loring Air Force Base, Limestone, Maine, to 83 at Phoeniz.
   Other reports:
   _East: Atlanta 63 fair; Boston 52 fair; Buffalo 51 fair;
Charleston, S.C. 66 partly cloudy; Cincinnati 54 fair; Cleveland 53
fair; Detroit 57 fair; Miami 79 fair; New York 58 fair;
Philadelphia 55 fair; Pittsburgh 53 fair; Portland, Maine 44 fair;
Washington 59 fair.
   _Central: Bismarck 40 fair; Chicago 62 fair; Dallas-Fort Worth
68 fair; Denver 58 partly cloudy; Des Moines 64 partly cloudy;
Indianapolis 57 fair; Minneapolis-St. Paul 61 fair; Nashville 60
fair; New Orleans 77 partly cloudy.
   _West: Albuquerque 61 fair; Anchorage 45 fair; Las Vegas 70
fair; Los Angeles 63 fair; Phoenix 83 fair; Salt Lake City 61 fair;
San Diego 62 fair; San Francisco 61 fair; Seattle 54 rain.
   _Canada: Montreal 46 partly cloudy; Toronto 54 fair.
</TEXT>
