<HEAD>Italians Oppose Docking Of Chemical Wastes</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MANFREDONIA, Italy (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Hundreds of students and fishermen
marched through the streets of this Adriatic port city on Tuesday
to protest the planned docking of a freighter bringing back
chemical wastes from Nigeria.
   The Deep Sea Carrier is one of three ships carrying Italian
industrial wastes that the government of Nigeria ordered returned
to Italy but that no Italian port wants to accept.
   Mayor Matteo Quitadamo of Manfredonia said local authorities
will try to block the docking of the Deep Sea Carrier unless the
national government announces a plan for the final disposal of the
waste elsewhere.
   Protests have also taken place in Leghorn and Ravenna, hampering
the government's efforts to bring the chemical wastes ashore
pending disposal.
