<1ST_LINE>r w AM-SugarLoans     09-27 0089</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Sugar Loans,80</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Agriculture Department Sets Price Support Loan Rates for Sugar</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The federal price support loan rates for
1988-crop U.S. sugar will be 18 cents per pound for domestically
grown raw cane sugar and 21.37 cents per pound for refined beet
sugar, the Agriculture Department said Tuesday.
   ``Both rates will be adjusted to reflect the processing location
and quality of the sugar,'' officials said.
   The 1988 cane support is unchanged from last year, and the beet
support is up slightly from 21.16 per pound.
</TEXT>
