<1ST_LINE>r w AM-SoybeanSupports     09-27 0121</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Soybean Supports,110</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Soybean Price Support Loan Rates Set At $4.77 Per Bushel</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Soybean price support loan rates for the 1988
crop will be $4.77 per bushel, unchanged from last year, the
Agriculture Department said Tuesday.
   That was also unchanged from the preliminary support rate
announced Aug. 12. All soybean producers will be eligible for the
loan program, officials said.
   Soybean market prices are currently around $8 per bushel, far
above the loan rate _ the amount farmers can borrow from the
government by using their crop as collateral.
   Prices rose as a result of smaller supplies this year. The
harvest, reduced by drought, is estimated at about 1.47 billion
bushels, down 23 percent from 1987 production.
</TEXT>
