<HEAD>Ads Tell Hunters To Vote Before They Shoot</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ALEXANDRIA, La. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The ``squirrel vote'' has become a
consideration in the five-candidate campaign for the U.S. House of
Representatives in Louisiana's meandering, largely rural 8th
Congressional District.
   Saturday's election coincides with the opening of Louisiana's
hunting season, and incumbent Rep. Clyde Holloway, R-La., is
running a radio ad urging squirrel hunters to vote absentee _ or in
person _ before heading for the forests.
   ``Don't let the squirrels take your vote away,'' says a
chipmunk-voiced announcer speaking on behalf of Holloway, who
claims the support of the National Rifle Association.
