   Arizona, New Hampshire and Maryland have the best
track record for creating new jobs and businesses and stimulating
growth of young companies in the last four years, according to a
new survey.
   Inc. magazine's annual report on the states concluded Monday
that the South and Southwest are thriving, but indicated some
industrial states are making a comeback thanks partly to programs
that use small amounts of tax dollars to foster private growth.
</TEXT>
