<HEAD>September Inflation Rate Highest This Year</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BRUSSELS, Belgium (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Belgium's annual inflation rate stood
at 1.21 percent in September, the highest this year, the government
reported Tuesday.
   The Belgian ministry of economy said the annual increase
compares to rates of 0.91 percent in August and 1.01 in July.
   Price increases were recorded for clothing, fresh fruit,
potatoes, restaurants and hotels, and tickets for soccer matches,
the ministry said.
