<1ST_LINE>u f AM-InsiderTrading     09-27 0146</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Insider Trading,0150</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>SEC Files Charges Against Former Toys R Us Executive</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Securities and Exchange Commission said
Tuesday that it has filed civil charges alleging insider trading by
a former executive of Toys R Us Inc.
   The civil action, filed by the SEC Monday in U.S. District Court
in New Jersey, alleges that James M. Markham, who has since
resigned as director of industrial purchasing for the Rochelle
Park, N.J., company, traded on confidential knowledge that the
company was experiencing stronger-than-expected Christmas sales in
November and December of 1987.
   Markham made profits of $40,000 by purchasing call options for
Toys R Us stock in November and December and selling them in
January after the company announced that its Christmas sales were
up 26.8 percent over 1985, the agency says.
   The SEC is seeking disgorgement of profits and an unspecified
civil penalty.
</TEXT>
