<1ST_LINE>u f AM-Fortune-Bilzerian     09-27 0193</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Fortune-Bilzerian,0202</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Acquisition Offer Made For Florida Financial Group</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CLEARWATER, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Fortune Financial Group Inc. announced
Tuesday it is studying a $140 million acquisition proposal by
financier Paul A. Bilzerian, who owns a 9.9 percent stake in the
banking company.
   The $35-a-share cash-tender offer will remain in effect until
Oct. 27, according to a statement by Fortune Financial. The
acquisition would be conducted by Bilzerian and an affiliated group.
   Fortune Financial stock jumped $2.75 a share to $30.50 in
national over-the-counter trading on Tuesday.
   Bilzerian owns 446,000, or 9.9 percent, of the current shares
outstanding of Fortune Financial, whose principal subsidiary,
Fortune Savings Bank, operates 45 banking offices in Florida.
   Bilzerian, who is based in Tampa, has been involved in a number
of takeover attempts, most recently the nearly $1.1 billion
acquisition of Singer Co. earlier this year.
   John B. Sweger, chairman of the board and chief executive
officer of Fortune Financial, said the offer and possible
alternatives would be studied by its board of directors and the
company's financial adviser, First Boston Corp.
   On June 30, Fortune Financial reported consolidated net worth of
$145.5 million, or $32.27 a share.
</TEXT>
